#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:4
msgid ""
"The value **y** and its combined standard uncertainty **u(y)** obtained "
"from the evaluation of the output quantity define the mean and the "
"standard deviation of a Gaussian distribution of possible values "
":math:`y^{'},`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:9
msgid ""
":math:`\\frac{1}{u(y)\\sqrt{2\\pi}}\\exp\\left( - \\frac{\\left( y^{'} - "
"y \\right)^{2}}{2\\ u^{2}(y)} \\right)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:11
msgid ""
"which is obtained from the application of the maximum information entropy"
" principle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:14
msgid ""
"Dependent on the size of the ratio **u(y)/y** it may happen that a part "
"of this distribution resides in the negative domain (:math:`y^{'}`\\ *< "
"0*). According to the Bayesian method it follows by using a positive "
"“model prior“, that this distribution function shall only have positive "
"values for positive :math:`y^{'}` values (:math:`y^{'}`: e.g. activity "
"values). Therefore, the part of the distribution in the negative domain "
"is cut at :math:`y^{'}`\\ *=* 0. Using this modified (cut) distribution "
"**expectation values of mean and standard deviation** can be determined "
"which are here called “\\ **best estimates according to Bayes**\\ ”. Let "
"ω be the value of the integral of the modified distribution function from"
" zero to infinity, with :math:`\\omega < 1`. The resulting expectation "
"values then are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:27
msgid "mean:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:29
msgid ""
":math:`\\widehat{y} = y + \\frac{u(y)\\ exp\\left( - \\frac{y^{2}}{2\\ "
"u^{2}(y)} \\right)}{\\omega\\sqrt{2\\pi}}` with :math:`\\omega = "
"\\Phi\\left( \\frac{y}{u(y)} \\right)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:32
msgid ""
"(:math:`\\Phi` is the (cumulative) distribution function of the "
"standardized normal distribution)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:35
msgid "standard deviation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:37
msgid ""
":math:`u\\left( \\widehat{y} \\right) = \\sqrt{u^{2}(y) - \\left( "
"\\widehat{y} - y \\right) \\bullet \\widehat{y}}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/special_methods/best_estimate.rst:39
msgid ""
"This guarantees that :math:`\\widehat{y}` always will have a positive "
"value."
msgstr ""

